      <item>
        <title>Kicksecure Firewall</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>While Kicksecure comes with no open ports by default, a firewall would be useful to protect the user from unwanted, unexpected ports opened by third-party software.</p>
<p>How this could be structured:</p>
<ul>
<li>kicksecure-shared-firewall</li>
<li>kicksecure-desktop-firewall [block all ports by default]</li>
<li>kicksecure-server-firewall [open port 22, which is SSH’s default port by default]
<ul>
<li>Maybe the server firewall should come last. If ever. Much later. Maybe not at all. Maybe server operators should take care of a firewall themselves.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
          <p><a href="https://forums.kicksecure.com/t/kicksecure-firewall/378/4">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
